SIMPLE: aquiline
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aquiline
<hw>Aq"ui*line</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>aquilinus</ets>, fr. <ets>aquila</ets> eagle: cf. F.
<ets>aquilin</ets>. See <er>Eagle</er>. ]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Belonging to or like an eagle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Curving; hooked; prominent, like the beak of an
eagle; -- applied particularly to the nose</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Terribly arched and <qex>aquiline</qex> his nose.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aquilon</ent>⟦br⟧
